Solanum furcatum

, while only rarely encountered in the Old World, is common in its native range in Chile (
Barboza et al. 2013
; 

Saerkinen
et al. 2015b

) and can be assessed as LC (Least Concern; Table 
7
) on a worldwide basis. In its native range in South America, it has an EOO of 1,809,315 km2 and is not of conservation concern.
